div.p:
Hee was a man for yeares but yong, The Authour. cropt off euen in the flower of his age, as more fit for heauen then the earth. Whilst he liued, he
was generally noted to bee a man of very great hope, and to be endued with many excellent parts, as well of grace as nature; whereof to giue thee onely a taste, hee was of a meeke spirit, a sober carriage, a discreete behauiour, a sound iudgement, and of such vncessant and indefatigable paines as promised (if the Lord had beene pleased to spare him life) much good and benefit to the Church of God: And which was the chiefest, and set the crowne vpon all the rest, hee was of a truely sincere, and a right gracious heart;
Ioh. 1.17. A true Nathaniel, an Israelite indeed in whom was no guile.
